Styling elements:
style is used to style the elements
1. inline Styling: Used inside the BODY. Inline styling in done by using style tag inside the element
<h3 style="text-align: center;">Heading 3</h3>

2.Internal Styling: style is used inside the HEAD

NOTES: inline styling will override the internal styling because inline is the last style

---STYLIGN ELEMENTS WITH CLASS ATRIBUTE---
We use class attribute to do same stylings for multiple elements

. means class

Creating a custom style 
 .my-custom-style{
            color: purple;
            font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif;
            font-size: 25px;
            text-align: center;
            background-color: yellow;
  }

using this custom style in ANY ELEMENT YOU WANT
<h3 class="my-custom-style">Heading 3</h3>

Now this style will apply to h3 element

--STYLING ELEMENTS USING ID ATTRIBUTE-----
-id attribute is used to style UNIQUE elements
# means id

--------Text Align-----
    <h3 style="text-align: center;">Heading 3</h3> : aligning in the center
    <h3 style="text-align: left;">Heading 3</h3> : aligning to the left
    <h3 style="text-align: right;">Heading 3</h3> : aligning to the right
    <h3 style="text-align: justify;">Heading 3</h3> : stretching out the text
---------backgorund color---------------
<body style="background-color: rgb(245, 251, 251);">

---br tag---
<br> is used to give break. it will take the next element to the next line

--hr tag----
<hr> is used to draw a horizontal line

--b tag---
b tag is used to make the text bold
 I live in <b>USA</b> 

 --i tag----
 i tag is used to make the text italic
 <i>USA</i> has freedom

 ---u tag---
 u tag is used to underline the texts
USA is very <u>rich</u> 


----ADDING IMAGE------
<img src="PATH OF THE IMAGE"> tag is used to add image

---SPACING IMAGES----
Margin: giving space around the image

  margin: 100px; --->>> 100 px space in all direction 

  margin-top: 100px;  --->>100 px space ONLY at the top
  margin-bottom: 100px; --->>100 px space ONLY at the buttom
  margin-right: 100px;--->>100 px space ONLY at the right
  margin-left: 100px;--->>100 px space ONLY at the left




Padding: giving spage INSIDE the image
  padding: 100px; --->>> 100 px space in all directions

  padding-top: 100px;-->>100 px space ONLY at the top
  padding-right: 100px;-->>100 px space ONLY at the right
  padding-bottom: 100px;-->>100 px space ONLY at the buttom
  padding-left: 100px;-->>100 px space ONLY at the left



---ADDING TEXT LINK-------

a tag is used to add a LINK

target="_blank"  --->>> open the link in a new window


---ADDING IMAGE LINK----
we use img tag inside a tag to create an image link

<a href="https://www.google.com/" target="_blank">   
        <img src="https://www.google.com/images/branding/googlelogo/1x/googlelogo_color_272x92dp.png" alt="google_logo">   
</a>


-----------EXTERNAL CSS-----------
This is the most common way
-easy to read, reusable css codes, seperating html and css files

STEPS:
1. create a css file: styles.css

2. add link in the head and give path of styles.css
<link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">

3. write your css code similar to internal css


----LIST---------
1. Unordered List (ul tag)
    List Item (li tag)

    <ul style="list-style-type: circle;"> -> circle images
    <ul style="list-style-type: lower-greek;"> -> greek symbos
    <ul style="list-style-type: square"> -> square

2. Ordered List (ol tag)
    List Item (li tag)

<ol type="i"> -> i, ii, iii


---WEB TABLES----
 <table> is used to create web TABLES

<thead> is used to create table header
<th> is used to create table header cell

<tr> is used to create TABLE ROW
<td> is used to create TABLE DATA

NOTES: there is no tag to create COLUMN direclty



----IFRAMES-----
iframes are pages within a page

<iframe> tag is usde to create iframes



---SECTION----
section is section
section is used to divide the contents into specific logical sections
sections do not have any visual immediate effect

------DIV----
div means division
div is used to divide the contents into specific logical sections
div do not have any visual immediate effect


---background image-------

background-image: url();
background-repeat: no-repeat; -> will not repeat teh same image. image will be used only once
background-size: WIDTH HEIGH;
background-size: 100% 100%;